> Tomato sauce is for way more than just pasta, people! Here, it shines atop bavette
> steak—but this is not your average marinara. Grape tomatoes caramelize and
> burst in the pan creating their own silky sauce. To take things to the next level,
> everything is served over a creamy, dreamy Parmesan risotto. It's perfect for
> elevating this already-rich and delicious meal—and for catching any extra sauce!

Wash and dry all produce. Mince @garlic{2%cloves}. Peel and mince @shallot{1}. In
a #small pot{}, combine @chicken stock concentrate{2} and @water{4%cups}. Bring
to a boil over high heat, then reduce to a simmer.

Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in a #large high-sided pan{} over medium heat. Add garlic
and cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}. Add @Arborio rice{3/4%cup} and
cook, stirring, until grains are translucent, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add 1/2 cup stock to pan with rice; stir until liquid has mostly absorbed. Repeat
with remaining stock—adding 1/2 cup at a time and stirring until liquid has
absorbed—until rice is al dente and mixture is creamy, ~{25-30%minutes}. Season
with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Once risotto has cooked 10 minutes, pat @bavette steak{10%oz} dry with #paper
towels{}; season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Heat a drizzle of
@olive oil{1%tbsp} in a second #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add steak and
cook to desired doneness, ~{5-7%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer to a
#cutting board{} to rest. Wipe out pan.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{} in pan used for steak over medium heat. Add
shallot, @grape tomatoes{4%oz}, and any resting juices from steak; season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook until tomatoes begin to burst, ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in
@balsamic vinegar{5%tsp} and @water{1/4%cup}. Simmer until slightly thickened,
~{3-5%minutes}. Remove from heat and stir in @butter{1%tbsp}.

Stir @Parmesan cheese{1/4%cup}, @crème fraîche{2%tbsp}, and @butter{1%tbsp} into
risotto. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Thinly slice steak against the grain.
Divide risotto between plates and top with steak. Spoon burst tomato sauce over
steak.